#. <section class="sutta" id="sn11.1"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn11.1:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 11"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 11"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.1:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga"
msgstr "1. The First Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn11.1:0.3"
msgid "1. Suvīrasutta"
msgstr "1. With Suvīra"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.216"></a>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.466"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.1:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "sn11.1:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

msgctxt "sn11.1:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "sn11.1:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "“Mendicants!”"

msgctxt "sn11.1:1.5"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "sn11.1:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.217"></a>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.467"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.1:2.1"
msgid "“Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, asurā deve abhiyaṃsu."
msgstr "“Once upon a time, mendicants, the demons marched against the gods."

msgctxt "sn11.1:2.2"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo suvīraṃ devaputtaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then Sakka, lord of gods, addressed the god Suvīra:"

msgctxt "sn11.1:2.3"
msgid "‘ete, tāta suvīra, asurā deve abhiyanti."
msgstr "‘Dear Suvīra, the demons march against the gods!"

msgctxt "sn11.1:2.4"
msgid "Gaccha, tāta suvīra, asure paccuyyāhī’ti."
msgstr "Go, and march against the demons!’"

#. VAR: āpādesi → āharesi (katthaci)
msgctxt "sn11.1:2.5"
msgid ""
"‘Evaṃ, bhaddantavā’ti kho, bhikkhave, suvīro devaputto sakkassa "
"devānamindassa paṭissutvā pamādaṃ āpādesi."
msgstr "‘Yes, lord,’ replied Suvīra. But he fell into negligence."

msgctxt "sn11.1:2.6"
msgid ""
"Dutiyampi kho, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo suvīraṃ devaputtaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "For a second time Sakka addressed Suvīra:"

msgctxt "sn11.1:2.7"
msgid "‘ete, tāta suvīra, asurā deve abhiyanti."
msgstr "‘Dear Suvīra, the demons march against the gods!"

msgctxt "sn11.1:2.8"
msgid "Gaccha, tāta suvīra, asure paccuyyāhī’ti."
msgstr "Go, and march against the demons!’"

msgctxt "sn11.1:2.9"
msgid ""
"‘Evaṃ, bhaddantavā’ti kho, bhikkhave, suvīro devaputto sakkassa "
"devānamindassa paṭissutvā dutiyampi pamādaṃ āpādesi."
msgstr ""
"‘Yes, lord,’ replied Suvīra. But for a second time he fell into negligence."

msgctxt "sn11.1:2.10"
msgid ""
"Tatiyampi kho, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo suvīraṃ devaputtaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "For a third time Sakka addressed Suvīra:"

msgctxt "sn11.1:2.11"
msgid "‘ete, tāta suvīra, asurā deve abhiyanti."
msgstr "‘Dear Suvīra, the demons march against the gods!"

msgctxt "sn11.1:2.12"
msgid "Gaccha, tāta suvīra, asure paccuyyāhī’ti."
msgstr "Go, and march against the demons!’"

msgctxt "sn11.1:2.13"
msgid ""
"‘Evaṃ, bhaddantavā’ti kho, bhikkhave, suvīro devaputto sakkassa "
"devānamindassa paṭissutvā tatiyampi pamādaṃ āpādesi."
msgstr ""
"‘Yes, lord,’ replied Suvīra. But for a third time he fell into negligence."

msgctxt "sn11.1:2.14"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo suvīraṃ devaputtaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr "Then Sakka addressed the god Suvīra in verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.1:3.1"
msgid "‘Anuṭṭhahaṃ avāyāmaṃ,"
msgstr "‘Suvīra, go to that place"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.1:3.2"
msgid "sukhaṃ yatrādhigacchati;"
msgstr "where you can achieve happiness"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.1:3.3"
msgid "Suvīra tattha gacchāhi,"
msgstr "without working for it or trying hard—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.1:3.4"
msgid "mañca tattheva pāpayā’ti."
msgstr "and take me with you!’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
#. VAR: Alasvassa → alasa’ssa (bj, pts1-2) | alasvāyaṃ (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn11.1:4.1"
msgid "‘Alasvassa anuṭṭhātā,"
msgstr "‘That a lazy man who does no work,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.1:4.2"
msgid "na ca kiccāni kāraye;"
msgstr "and doesn’t do his duty,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.1:4.3"
msgid "Sabbakāmasamiddhassa,"
msgstr "should fulfill all his desires:"

# See BB for readings. Note that Cone acknowledges disati in the sense of “grant”, citing this passage.
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.1:4.4"
msgid "taṃ me sakka varaṃ disā’ti."
msgstr "Sakka, grant me this boon!’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.468"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.1:5.1"
msgid "‘Yatthālaso anuṭṭhātā,"
msgstr "‘Suvīra, go to that place"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.1:5.2"
msgid "accantaṃ sukhamedhati;"
msgstr "where a lazy man who does no work"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.1:5.3"
msgid "Suvīra tattha gacchāhi,"
msgstr "prospers in unending happiness—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.1:5.4"
msgid "mañca tattheva pāpayā’ti."
msgstr "and take me with you!’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.1:6.1"
msgid "‘Akammunā devaseṭṭha,"
msgstr "‘O Sakka, best of gods,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.1:6.2"
msgid "sakka vindemu yaṃ sukhaṃ;"
msgstr "that we might find the happiness"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.1:6.3"
msgid "Asokaṃ anupāyāsaṃ,"
msgstr "that’s sorrowless, unstressed:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.1:6.4"
msgid "taṃ me sakka varaṃ disā’ti."
msgstr "Sakka, grant me this boon!’"

# See BB for the problems with this verse. The Chinese texts at both SA2 43 (活) and SA 1114 (生) appears to support jivati rather than jiyati. Bingenheimer at sa-2.43 has “Have you ever seen or heard of someone who, without effort, ​attains happiness in life?” Both the Cinese texts have more lines than the Pali, and given that the Pali has five lines, it seems likely the text has suffered loss. I translate according to what I guess the meaning to have been.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.1:7.1"
msgid "‘Sace atthi akammena,"
msgstr "‘If there exists anyone anywhere"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.1:7.2"
msgid "koci kvaci na jīvati;"
msgstr "who can can live happily without working,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.1:7.3"
msgid "Nibbānassa hi so maggo,"
msgstr "that surely would be extinguishment’s path!"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.1:7.4"
msgid "suvīra tattha gacchāhi;"
msgstr "Go there, Suvīra,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.1:7.5"
msgid "Mañca tattheva pāpayā’ti."
msgstr "and take me with you!’"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.469"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.1:8.1"
msgid ""
"So hi nāma, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo sakaṃ puññaphalaṃ upajīvamāno "
"devānaṃ tāvatiṃsānaṃ issariyādhipaccaṃ rajjaṃ kārento uṭṭhānavīriyassa "
"vaṇṇavādī bhavissati."
msgstr ""
"So, mendicants, even Sakka, lord of gods—while living off of the fruit of "
"his good and bad deeds, and ruling as sovereign lord over these gods of the "
"Thirty-Three—will speak in praise of initiative and energy."

msgctxt "sn11.1:8.2"
msgid ""
"Idha kho taṃ, bhikkhave, sobhetha, yaṃ tumhe evaṃ svākkhāte dhammavinaye "
"pabbajitā samānā uṭṭhaheyyātha ghaṭeyyātha vāyameyyātha appattassa pattiyā "
"anadhigatassa adhigamāya, asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"But since you have gone forth in such a well explained teaching and "
"training, it would be truly beautiful for you to try hard, strive, and make "
"an effort to attain the unattained, achieve the unachieved, and realize the "
"unrealized!”"
